{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/all-about-conda","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I decided to create this page because I often</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.conda.io/projects/conda/en/stable/user-guide/cheatsheet.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Anaconda cheatsheet</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/code/anaconda-in-vscode-terminal\">My note</a> on how to install Anaconda in VSCode terminal</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"common-tasks\" style=\"position:relative;\">Common tasks<a href=\"#common-tasks\" aria-label=\"common tasks permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>There is probably an environment where I already have PyTorch installed but <strong>how to find the environment with one specific package installed</strong>? Of course this is about some big packages like TensorFlow or PyTorch or something with native dependencies where it's more of a hassle to create a new one.</p>\n<p>So list configured environments with</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">conda info <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--envs</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>and then search for the package</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">conda list <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-n</span> diffusers torch <span class=\"token comment\"># last positional argument is a regex</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># so instead you can apply your bash-fu</span>\nconda list <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-n</span> diffusers <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">grep</span> torch</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\">Examples<a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>My environments I created in the following projects</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/blog/starcode\">Transformers and PyTorch</a></li>\n<li>Also <a href=\"/ai/agent-emotion-model\">PyTorch</a>, but in WSL2 and this version is craving for <code class=\"language-text\">CUDA_HOME</code></li>\n<li><a href=\"/ai/my-faces-dataset\">Diffusers</a> from Hugging Face</li>\n<li><a href=\"/ai/unsupervised-image-classification-with-gan\">TensorFlow 2.12</a> on Windows can only be installed in WSL2</li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"I decided to create this page because I often Anaconda cheatsheet My note on how to install Anaconda in VSCode terminal Common tasks There…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#common-tasks\">Common tasks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#examples\">Examples</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"August 05, 2024","published":"August 05, 2024","lastModified":"August 05, 2024","title":"All about Conda","subtitle":null,"section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/all-about-conda.md","url":"/blog/all-about-conda","next":{"excerpt":"Some time ago I played with setting up Anaconda in VS Code, but this time I want to upgrade Git for Windows and run it from Alacritty…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/alacritty-everywhere.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Alacritty everywhere","date":"2024-08-25T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"1162d8cf-dc8c-5d3a-bf38-969825afe19d"},"previous":{"excerpt":"State representation Make sure that graphical representation matches with internal data which usually means values in tensors. If it's a 2D…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/simple-reinforcement-learning.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Simple Reinforcement Learning","date":"2024-08-05T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"baabef51-5f03-544c-b6bc-edce76feba2f"},"recentArticles":[{"excerpt":"When humans create real artificial intelligence, will it need sleep? This was my thought just before I fell asleep. I was thinking about Lex…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/should-ai-sleep.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Should AI sleep?","date":"2024-09-03T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"6a224dca-f97f-56c1-b7e3-59f1cc70ecc8"},{"excerpt":"Some time ago I played with setting up Anaconda in VS Code, but this time I want to upgrade Git for Windows and run it from Alacritty…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/alacritty-everywhere.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Alacritty everywhere"